    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Randomized controlled trial assessing the safety and benefits of shortening preoperative
      fasts on intubated ICU patients undergoing tracheotomy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients undergoing bedside tracheotomy in an ICU are enrolled and randomized into two
      groups. Arm A receive a standard fast of at least 6 hours. Arm B receive a shortened fast of
      only 45 minutes, just before the surgery begins. Patients will be monitored for aspiration,
      pneumonia and our ability to delivery better nutrition as a result of the intervention.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
